  "response": "Here are some home remedies that may help with stress-related lip bumps:\n\n1. Cold compress\n- Reduces inflammation\n- Helps soothe irritation\n- Can help reduce swelling\n\n2. Aloe vera gel\n- Natural anti-inflammatory properties\n- Promotes healing\n- Provides cooling relief\n\n3. Honey\n- Antibacterial properties\n- Helps moisturize lips\n- Can reduce inflammation\n\n4. Tea tree oil (diluted)\n- Has antimicrobial properties\n- Can help dry out bumps\n- Should always be diluted before use\n\n5. Chamomile tea compress\n- Reduces inflammation\n- Soothes irritated skin\n- Has calming properties\n\n6. Coconut oil\n- Moisturizes lips\n- Has natural healing properties\n- Can help reduce infection risk\n\n7. Stay hydrated\n- Helps overall skin health\n- Can reduce stress-related symptoms\n- Supports healing process\n\nAdditional tips:\n- Reduce stress through relaxation techniques\n- Maintain good lip hygiene\n- Avoid touching or picking at bumps\n- Use gentle lip care products\n\nIf bumps persist or become painful, consult a healthcare professional to rule out other conditions.",
